Node.Notes: Uncertain. See commentaries. Tree assumes: ones who were complaining about hardship in the ears of Yahweh.
Uncertain. Many mss read eyes, which would yield: P-PP clause: [it was] evil in the eyes of Yahweh.
Uncertain. Assumes: our eyes [look at nothing] except at the manna.
This particular noun occurs only once and could mean youth or chosen men. The Syriac and Targums go with from youth and the Samaritan Pentateuch and Septuagint go with chosen men.
